    "description_text": "Company Description\nThe Microsoft Consulting & Innovation team operates in a rapidly changing environment. You will learn quickly through a personal training program and grow in your position with hands-on experience by working on projects together with colleagues. You will receive guidance from an assigned Development Manager (DM) who will help you with your development, career and achieving your personal goals. You will also be assigned a buddy who will show you around the world of KPMG and MCI. \nWithin KPMG and MCI, training is high on our lists. You have the opportunity to attend training courses and learn about and get certified for Microsoft technology. The team also undertakes many social activities together, such as breakfast sessions or events with sporting activities. The team now has more than 60 employees, has 17 different nationalities and is growing! \nWe are looking to expand our Microsoft Dynamics 365 team, which consists of Business Consultants who are involved on a daily basis with implementing Microsoft Dynamics 365 products such as Finance & Operations, Customer Engagement and Power Platform. Do you also want to work at a major international player in the field of Microsoft Dynamics 365 consultancy and carry out cool projects at customer organizations together with a fun and diverse team? Then read on! \nJob Description\nAt KPMG’s Microsoft Consulting & Innovation team, you won’t just be joining a company you’ll be stepping into a community of forward-thinkers, problem-solvers, and tech enthusiasts who are passionate about making a real difference. Here, your ideas matter, your growth is prioritized, and your potential is unleashed.\nFrom day one, you’ll be immersed in a dynamic environment where innovation meets purpose. You’ll work on high-impact projects for leading organizations, using Microsoft Dynamics 365 to solve complex challenges in finance, supply chain, and beyond. You’ll be supported by a personal Development Manager and a buddy who’ll guide you through your journey, while you build your skills through hands-on experience and top-tier training.\nBut it’s not just about work, it’s about thriving. Whether it’s breakfast sessions, sports events, or team socials, we believe in celebrating success together. With over 60 colleagues from 17 nationalities, you’ll be part of a diverse, inclusive team that values collaboration, creativity, and going the extra mile.\nIf you’re ready to accelerate your career, challenge yourself, and help shape the digital future. Join our fast-growing Microsoft Consulting & Innovation team at KPMG, where innovation meets impact. As a Senior Consultant in Supply Chain Management, you’ll work on transformative projects that help global organizations optimize their operations using Microsoft Dynamics 365.\nQualifications\n3+ years experience in implementation of ERP solutions\nStrong interest in supply chain modules like Production, Advanced Warehouse, or Transportation.\nStrong analytical skills and a proactive mindset.\nPassion for new technology innovation, and making a real difference by delivering high quality\nRelevant Microsoft certifications.\nAdditional Information\nCompetitive salary between € 3.245,- en € 5050,-, a bonus, a fixed expense allowance and a working from home allowance.\n30 vacation days (on a full-time basis) and the option to buy more days or sell your vacation days.\nAt KPMG we work hybrid, so you can work from home or at the office.\nA completely furnished home office.\nReimbursement of your travel expenses with a NS business card or travel allowance / A lease car or a mobility budget. (Please select the right option for this vacancy)\nA laptop and iPhone which also can be used privately.\nPension accrual without a compulsory personal contribution. \nChoice to pick from different courses which contribute to your own personal and professional development.\nDiversity networks in the areas of pride, gender, ability, cultural diversity, and generations that regularly organize various activities to celebrate differences!\nFocus on well-being! There is a gym at the Amstelveen office or you can get a discount for a gym near your house and you get access to different health and/or vitality programs.\n‘Together’ is one of our core values. So you can count on different social activities, like team events, drinks with colleagues and events with all your KPMG colleagues.",
